                      },
                      "date": 2024
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "#doi:10.1016/j.nima.2023.169001"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USABNL",
                "1USATEM",
                "1USAORL"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAORL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The PT-2 pneumatic tube of the High",
                "Flux Isotope Reactor (HFIR) at the Neutron Activation",
                "Analysis laboratory (NAA) of Oak Ridge National",
                "Laboratory."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The measured thermal and epithermal neutron",
                "fluxes at the irradiation location are 4.59*10**13",
                "n/cm2/s and 1.96*10**11 n/cm2/s respectively for 235U,",
                "and 4.43*10**13 n/cm2/s and 3.24*10**11 n/cm2/s",
                "respectively for 239Pu. The energy ranges for",
                "epithermal neutrons are 0.1 eV to 10 keV for 239Pu",
                "and 1 eV to 10 keV for 235U. The neutron fluxes are",
                "measured using manganese and gold activation foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 44% relative efficiency, ORTEC p-type",
                "coaxial HPGe detector with an aluminum end cap."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 235U sample consists of 252.72 nanograms of",
                "natural uranium nitrate in an Inductively Coupled",
                "Plasma calibration solution. The 239Pu sample",
                "consists of 301.3 nanogram of National Institute of",
                "Standards and Technology (NIST) Certified Reference",
                "Material (CRM-137)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Each sample is irradiated for 30 s, and then",
                "transported to the detector chamber using the",
                "pneumatic tube transfer system which introduces a",
                "20-s delay prior to the gamma-ray measurement. The",
                "gamma rays are measured with a coaxial HPGe detector.",
                "Each sample is placed at 33 cm above the detector and",
                "measured for 30 s."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainty in the expected gamma-ray",
                "yield is evaluated through a quadrature sum of",
                "uncertainties in the total number of nuclides present",
                "at the end of irradiation, the absolute efficiency of",
                "the HPGe, and and the gamma emission intensity."
              ]
            }
          ],
